The paper deals with image compressive sensing reconstruction, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SP). The proposed method involves sparse representation modeling, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of principle component analysis (PCA), which is a popular method in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
